Author-Name:    Chambers, Marcus J
Author-Name:  Bailey, Roy E
Title:   A Theory of Commodity Price Fluctuations. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 924-57
Issue: 5
Volume: 104
Year: 1996
Month:  October 
Abstract:
  This paper studies the price fluctuations of storable commodities that
 are traded in open markets and are subject to random shocks to demand or,
 more particularly, to supply. It relaxes the common assumption that the
 shocks are identically and independently distributed in favor of
 temporally dependent and periodic disturbances. The existence of a unique
 stationary rational expectations equilibrium is demonstrated for each of
 the models analyzed and testable implications of the models are derived.
 An illustrative empirical investigation is then undertaken for the model
 with periodic disturbances using monthly time-series observations for
 seven commodities over the period 1960-93.  Copyright 1996 by University of Chicago Press.
