Author-Name:    Persson, Torsten
Author-Name:  Tabellini, Guido
Title:   Federal Fiscal Constitutions: Risk Sharing and Redistribution. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 979-1009
Issue: 5
Volume: 104
Year: 1996
Month:  October 
Abstract:
  This paper studies the political and economic determinants of regional
 public transfers. Specifically, it focuses on how such transfers are
 shaped by alternative fiscal constitutions, where a constitution is an
 allocation of fiscal instruments across different levels of governments
 plus a procedure for the collective choice of these instruments. Realistic
 restrictions on fiscal instruments introduce a trade-off between risk
 sharing and redistribution. Different constitutions produce very different
 results. In particular, a federal social insurance scheme, chosen by
 voting, provides overinsurance, whereas an intergovernmental transfer
 scheme, chosen by bargaining, provides underinsurance.  Copyright 1996 by University of Chicago Press.
